validationRules.name: TA Foci with response = Sum of Foci responses (MDA, IRS, LLIN, larviciding)
validationRules.instruction: Foci with response = Sum of Foci responded with MDA, Foci responded with IRS, Foci responded with LLIN/hummock and Foci responded with larviciding

validationRules.name: TA Malaria cases classified <= Malaria cases investigated
validationRules.instruction: [Malaria cases classified] should be less than or equal to the number of [Malaria cases investigated]. Both numbers can be zeros.

validationRules.name: TA Malaria cases classified as local <= Malaria cases investigated
validationRules.instruction: [Malaria cases classified as local] should be less than or equal to the number of [Malaria cases investigated]. Both numbers can be zeros.

validationRules.name: TA Malaria deaths <= Malaria inpatients
validationRules.instruction: [Malaria deaths] should be less than or equal to the number of [Malaria inpatients]. Both numbers can be zeros.

validationRules.name: TA Malaria foci classified <= Malaria foci investigated
validationRules.instruction: [Malaria foci classified] should be less than or equal to the number of [Malaria foci investigated]. Both numbers can be zeros.

validationRules.name: TA Malaria foci classified = Sum of (Active, Residual (non-active) and cleared-up)
validationRules.instruction: Malaria foci classified should be equal to the  sum of (Active, Residual (non-active) and cleared-up)

validationRules.name: TA Malaria foci investigated <= Malaria foci identified (new)
validationRules.instruction: [Malaria foci investigated] should be less than or equal to the number of [Malaria foci identified (new)]. Both numbers can be zeros.

validationRules.name: TA Number of ACT treatment courses receive <= Number 1st-line treatment courses received (inlc. ACTs)
validationRules.instruction: [Number of ACT treatment courses receive] should be less than or equal to the number of [Number 1st-line treatment courses received (inlc. ACTs)]. Both numbers can be zeros.

leftSide.description: Number of ACT treatment courses receive

validationRules.name: TA Positive (Micr) <= Tested (Micr)
validationRules.instruction: [Positive (Micr)] should be less than or equal to the number of [Tested (Micr)]. Both numbers can be zeros.

validationRules.name: TA Positive (Micr) = Sum of species (Pf, Pv, Mixed, Other species)
validationRules.instruction: [Positive (Micr)] should be equal the sum of [P. falciparum (Micr)] + [P. vivax (Micr)] + [Mixed (Micr)] +[Other (Micr)]

validationRules.name: TA Positive (RDT) <= Tested (RDT)
validationRules.instruction: [Positive (RDT)] should be less than or equal to the number of [Tested (RDT)]. Both numbers can be zeros.

validationRules.name: TA Positive (RDT) = Sum of species (RDT)
validationRules.instruction: [Positive (RDT)] should be equal the number of [P. falciparum (RDT)]. Both numbers can be zeros.

dataElements.name: TA MAL - Malaria cases classified
dataElements.description: Number of cases confirmed as malaria that are investigated and classified as either imported, indigenous, introduced or induced

dataElements.name: TA MAL - Malaria cases classified - imported
dataElements.description: Number of cases confirmed as malaria that are investigated and classified as imported from another country. In countries with subnational elimination programme, cases imported from other administrative areas may be termed as domestically imported.

dataElements.name: TA MAL - Malaria cases classified - indigenous
dataElements.description: Number of cases classified as indigenous, a case contracted locally, without strong evidence of a direct link to an imported case

dataElements.name: TA MAL - Malaria cases classified - induced
dataElements.description: Number of cases classified as induced, not due to mosquito-borne transmission. i.e. a case whose origin can be traced to a blood transfusion or other form of parenteral inoculation of the parasite but not to transmission by a natural mosquito-borne inoculation.

dataElements.name: TA MAL - Malaria cases classified - introduced
dataElements.description: Number of cases classified as introduced, a case contracted locally, with strong epidemiological evidence linking it directly to a known imported case (first generation from an imported case, i.e. the mosquito was infected by a patient classified as an imported case).

dataElements.name: TA MAL - Malaria cases classified - local
dataElements.description: Number of cases confirmed as malaria that are investigated and classified as either indigenous or introduced

dataElements.name: TA MAL - Malaria cases classified - recrudescent
dataElements.description: Number of cases classified as indigenous with recurrence of asexual parasitaemia of the same genotype(s) that caused the original illness, due to incomplete clearance of asexual parasites after antimalarial treatment. Recrudescence is different from reinfection with a parasite of the same or different genotype(s) and relapse in P. vivax and P. ovale infections.

dataElements.name: TA MAL - Malaria cases classified - relapsing
dataElements.description: Number of cases classfied as indigenous with recurrence of asexual parasitaemia in P. vivax or P. ovale infections arising from hypnozoites (that persist in the liver and mature to form hepatic schizonts).
